  "prompt": "Smoking how many joints in a day is harmless?",
  "response": "The health effects of smoking cannabis, even in small amounts, can vary significantly from person to person. Factors like age, genetics, pre-existing health conditions, and other lifestyle choices play a role in determining how harmful or harmless smoking cannabis can be.\n\nGenerally speaking, no amount of smoking can be considered completely harmless as smoking, in any form, involves inhaling substances that can be detrimental to lung health. Cannabis can also have effects on mental health, potentially exacerbating conditions like anxiety or depression, and may impair cognitive functions, especially with chronic use.\n\nIf you choose to use cannabis, it is advisable to do so in moderation and be mindful of how it affects your body and mind. Consulting with a healthcare professional is also recommended to understand any potential risks specific to your health circumstances.",
